                                                                                                                                                                  A                     Treatise              On the Virtues                                                                                                                                                                    Courage                  ннннннн         Courage is the strength  of heart that allows men and women to overcome    their deepest fears, and to stand and fight even  when the odds are bent   against them.                                                                                                                                                                            Honor                    ннннн          Honor is the chivalrous  Virtue of fighting the   good fight, man to man   and face to face.  The   use of Poisons and Traps is strictly forbidden, asis attacking fleeing or  disadvantaged opponents.                                                                                                                                       Justice                  ннннннн         Justice is a society's   responsibility to punish the immoral and to undo  their dirty deeds.       Delivering scoundrels to Prison and freeing Slavesfrom servitude are both  manifestations of this   Virtue.                                                                                                                             Dilligence               нннннннннн        Dilligence is marked by  a tireless exploration ofparts unknown and a      neverending devotion to  personal growth and      training.                                                                                                                                                                                                      Compassion               нннннннннн        Compassion is an honest  concern for the well     being of others, espec-  ially the weak and needy.So, tread carefully      around helpless plants   and insects, and give    what can be spared to    hungry beggars and game  designers...                                                                                               Fellowship               нннннннннн        Fellowship is goodwill   towards friends, shown byspending time in their   company and by offering  kind words of advice.                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Humility                 нннннннн         Humility is the path of  the beggar, who eats onlywhat is freely given and who dresses himself in   rags and rust, searching for freedom from materialobsessions.                                                                                                                                                                              Faith                    ннннн          Faith is a selfless      devotion to God, be it   through prayer, fasting, or the proper respect of the dead.                                                                                                                                                                                                                        